.TH "svc_find_xprt" 9 "svc_find_xprt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_find_xprt \- find an RPC transport instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct svc_xprt *" svc_find_xprt
.BI "(struct svc_serv *serv "  ","
.BI "const char *xcl_name "  ","
.BI "struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const sa_family_t af "  ","
.BI "const unsigned short port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "serv" 12
pointer to svc_serv to search
.IP "xcl_name" 12
C string containing transport's class name
.IP "net" 12
owner net pointer
.IP "af" 12
Address family of transport's local address
.IP "port" 12
transport's IP port number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the transport instance pointer for the endpoint accepting
connections/peer traffic from the specified transport class,
address family and port.

Specifying 0 for the address family or port is effectively a
wild-card, and will result in matching the first transport in the
service's list that has a matching class name.
